WEBVTT

00:43.478 --> 00:45.567
Who's that? He looks familiar.

00:45.610 --> 00:47.047
That is Armie Hammer.

00:47.090 --> 00:49.005
-He starred in <i>Lone Ranger.
-How old is he?</i>

00:49.049 --> 00:50.267
No, not the old one.

00:50.311 --> 00:52.095
This was a remake
just a few years ago.

00:52.139 --> 00:55.185
What was his issue?
Cannibalism, allegedly.

00:55.229 --> 00:57.144
Bite play, stuff like that.

00:57.187 --> 00:58.623
So how was he canceled?

00:58.667 --> 01:01.583
He got dropped from movies,
from the stage.

01:01.626 --> 01:03.411
-His agents dropped him.
-What are we talking about?

01:03.454 --> 01:05.195
-You're late.
-Sorry. I had paperwork.

01:05.239 --> 01:08.111
Well, you just have to listen
and catch up, won't you?

01:08.155 --> 01:09.547
God, are you in a bad mood?

01:09.591 --> 01:11.332
Nope, I just know you're
gonna disagree with me.

01:12.159 --> 01:14.204
Oh, no. Are you serious?
What?

01:14.248 --> 01:15.553
You're gonna clear these guys?

01:15.597 --> 01:17.555
No, they're-they're
not all just guys.

01:17.599 --> 01:18.643
Really? Where are the women?

01:18.687 --> 01:20.384
I got one right here.

01:20.428 --> 01:22.821
I spotted one...
Yep, Henrietta Michaels,

01:22.865 --> 01:25.302
former Professor
at Northwestern.

01:25.346 --> 01:27.130
She was fired for using a word

01:27.174 --> 01:29.828
which was misunderstood
by her students.

01:29.872 --> 01:33.093
She wants
to defend herself on TV

01:33.136 --> 01:34.529
so she can get her job back.

01:34.572 --> 01:36.966
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
That sounds like good TV.

01:37.009 --> 01:39.534
So four dozen guys accused
of rape and harassment,

01:39.577 --> 01:41.666
-and one woman.
-Oh, come on, Marissa.

01:41.710 --> 01:42.972
People are getting canceled
without a trial,

01:43.015 --> 01:44.408
no evidence
presented against them.

01:44.452 --> 01:45.496
-Because they did it.
-Maybe they did,

01:45.540 --> 01:46.671
maybe they didn't.

01:46.715 --> 01:48.151
or maybe it's more nuanced.

01:48.195 --> 01:50.414
Oh, my God, you sound
like that Canadian guy.

01:50.458 --> 01:51.937
The one who wrote
the book about that thing.

01:51.981 --> 01:53.548
If I knew what that meant,
maybe I'd be offended.

01:53.591 --> 01:55.245
You want to play
cancel-culture cop.

01:55.289 --> 01:57.508
No. I want to play judge.

01:57.552 --> 01:59.249
Oh, my God.
-Think about it.

01:59.293 --> 02:01.991
There are lots of reasons these
accusations never go to trial.

02:02.034 --> 02:04.298
The victims finally get to
accuse the victimizer

02:04.341 --> 02:05.864
face to face.

02:05.908 --> 02:07.866
-What if they don't want to?
-That's their choice.

02:07.910 --> 02:09.999
And the victimizer
gets the court to himself?

02:10.042 --> 02:12.044
To say whatever
bullshit he wants.

02:12.088 --> 02:13.481
This is a bad joke.

02:13.524 --> 02:15.047
-You're undercutting MeToo.
-No, no,

02:15.091 --> 02:17.615
-no, we're giving MeToo teeth.
That's right.

02:17.659 --> 02:20.357
If it relies on mob rule,
it'll exhaust itself.

02:20.401 --> 02:22.185
Okay. All right.
Mom, Dad, please.

02:22.229 --> 02:24.622
I hate when you fight.
Let's get back to work

02:24.666 --> 02:26.146
Who's up first?

02:26.189 --> 02:29.279
-Who's this guy?
-Oh, uh. Joey Battle.

02:29.323 --> 02:31.760
-Stand-up.
-Oh, God, you mean
Louis C.K. Two.

02:31.803 --> 02:33.065
-What'd he do?
He masturbated

02:33.109 --> 02:36.112
in front of two women
in a green room.

02:36.156 --> 02:38.027
To be fair, he did ask
for permission first.

02:38.070 --> 02:40.247
Seriously? If he did,
he didn't wait for a "yes."

02:40.290 --> 02:41.813
But he did not assault anyone.

02:41.857 --> 02:44.729
Oh. Are we really setting
the bar that low?

02:44.773 --> 02:46.340
Let's compromise.
We'll do both.

02:46.383 --> 02:49.734
-Both?
-Yeah, this guy
and, uh, Marissa's idea.

02:49.778 --> 02:52.084
The academic, uh,
Henrietta what's-her-name.

02:52.128 --> 02:54.174
Henrietta Michaels.
-That wasn't my idea.

02:54.217 --> 02:55.914
-When can we start?
You really think

02:55.958 --> 02:57.655
-there's time to do both?
We'll make the time.

02:57.699 --> 02:59.527
-Let's just schedule it.

02:59.570 --> 03:00.745
<i>That's my time, guys.</i>

03:00.789 --> 03:02.791
Thank you very much.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.884
June, you were great.

03:08.927 --> 03:11.582
The drinks are watered down,
so I know you're not drunk.

03:11.626 --> 03:13.236
No. You're funny.

03:13.280 --> 03:14.933
It's just this club sucks.

03:15.717 --> 03:17.109
Is this about Joey Battle?

03:17.153 --> 03:18.850
How'd you know?

03:18.894 --> 03:21.244
Reporters are the only ones
who approach me nowadays.

03:21.288 --> 03:22.811
I'm not a reporter.

03:23.638 --> 03:26.075
The last time I spoke out
about Joey Battle,

03:26.118 --> 03:27.381
this happened to me.

03:27.424 --> 03:29.426
I mean, I was on my way
to a serious career,

03:29.470 --> 03:31.036
and that scumbag derailed me.

03:31.080 --> 03:33.865
Not just off the tracks,
like buried under them.

03:33.909 --> 03:36.259
By testifying,
you'd get the truth out.

03:36.303 --> 03:37.695
Did you say "truth"?

03:37.739 --> 03:40.437
I thought we were talking
about a reality TV show.

03:40.481 --> 03:42.831
Millions of people could see it.

03:42.874 --> 03:45.094
I mean, I don't even know
the whole truth.

03:45.137 --> 03:47.531
When the story about Joey
was about to break,

03:47.575 --> 03:48.793
he reached out to me
on Facebook.

03:48.837 --> 03:50.360
And you know what he said?

03:50.404 --> 03:52.623
He said, "I'm sorry for shoving
you into a closet."

03:52.667 --> 03:54.016
He shoved you into a closet?

03:54.059 --> 03:56.148
No, with me, he just
jacked off into a plant.

03:56.192 --> 03:58.847
I can't help but think, though,
"who did he shove into a closet

03:58.890 --> 04:00.152
and what happened to her?"

04:00.196 --> 04:02.807
So you should
testify against him.

04:02.851 --> 04:05.027
-Bring that out.
-This is just another way
for Battle

04:05.070 --> 04:07.116
to get his career back.
I'm not participating in that.

04:07.159 --> 04:08.552
What if it wasn't?

04:08.596 --> 04:11.251
What if he was actually
confronted with his crime?

04:11.294 --> 04:12.469
It'll never happen.

04:12.513 --> 04:14.558
People like Battle win.

04:14.602 --> 04:16.212
People like me lose.

04:16.256 --> 04:19.171
But, you know what?
This is my consolation prize.

04:19.215 --> 04:21.043
His Wikipedia page.

04:21.086 --> 04:23.524
He's no longer
the comedian saint.

04:23.567 --> 04:26.614
Now he's Mr. Masturbater
in the greenroom.

04:36.232 --> 04:37.581
Who's defending Battle?

04:37.625 --> 04:39.888
The comedian?
David is.

04:39.931 --> 04:41.716
David Cord.
Why?

04:41.759 --> 04:43.326
He's a lawyer.

04:43.370 --> 04:45.937
My guess is he wants to
make an issue of cancel culture.

04:45.981 --> 04:48.200
Then I want to prosecute him.

04:48.244 --> 04:49.419
-Really?
-Yeah.

04:49.463 --> 04:51.029
I'm gonna rip him a new one.

04:51.073 --> 04:53.467
-David or the comedian?
-Both.

04:53.510 --> 04:55.207
Oh, that's the spirit.

04:55.251 --> 04:57.732
What about the other case--
the, uh, academic lady?

04:57.775 --> 05:00.212
That's different.
She shouldn't have been fired.

05:00.256 --> 05:02.606
No, you want to prosecute one,
you have to prosecute the other.

05:02.650 --> 05:05.392
-Why?
-Because I'm unpredictable.

05:05.435 --> 05:06.436
Haven't you heard?

05:06.480 --> 05:08.264
It's about cancel culture.

05:08.308 --> 05:11.267
-Have to explore all sides.
-I don't want to explore
all sides.

05:11.311 --> 05:12.921
Well, this isn't about
what you want.

05:12.964 --> 05:14.749
Let's go into court.

05:15.576 --> 05:18.796
<i>Nobody move! Get down!
Get down on the ground!</i>

05:18.840 --> 05:21.408
<i>Get down!
This party is a violation</i>

05:21.451 --> 05:23.497
<i>of COVID quarantine rules!</i>

05:23.540 --> 05:24.933
<i>Turn that fucking music off!</i>

05:25.977 --> 05:27.631
Did you see that?

05:27.675 --> 05:29.894
<i>Is something funny here?</i>

05:29.938 --> 05:31.505
<i>What the hell's so funny?</i>

05:31.548 --> 05:33.985
<i>Nobody said anything.
-Come here!</i>

05:34.029 --> 05:36.727
Ms. Farrow, where
was this taken?

05:36.771 --> 05:38.250
At a friend's house party.

05:38.294 --> 05:41.123
It was a great day
until somebody called the cops.

05:41.166 --> 05:43.778
And the cop that
arrived was, uh,

05:43.821 --> 05:45.432
Officer McFinley, yes?

05:45.475 --> 05:47.390
Yes.

05:47.434 --> 05:49.087
<i>Get down. Get down over here!</i>

05:49.131 --> 05:51.742
<i>Ow! Hey, let me go.</i>

05:51.786 --> 05:54.049
<i>-I didn't do anything wrong!
-Get down!</i>

05:54.092 --> 05:56.225
<i>-Ow! Let me go.
-Get the fuck down!</i>

05:56.268 --> 05:58.183
<i>-Ow! Ow, you're hurting me.
-Stay down!</i>

05:58.227 --> 06:01.230
<i>-Ow!
-Get down! Stop resisting.</i>

06:01.273 --> 06:05.800
<i></i>

06:05.843 --> 06:07.236
<i>No...</i>

06:10.500 --> 06:11.936
What happened next?

06:13.285 --> 06:14.983
I ran to her.

06:16.898 --> 06:18.378
She wasn't breathing.

06:19.640 --> 06:21.816
When the paramedics arrived,

06:21.859 --> 06:23.383
she was dead.

06:24.471 --> 06:27.778
You know that Antoinette's
family is suing the Chicago PD

06:27.822 --> 06:29.214
for five million dollars?

06:29.258 --> 06:30.520
Yes.

06:30.564 --> 06:34.089
If it were up to me,
it'd be ten times that.

06:40.443 --> 06:41.575
Thank you, Miss Farrow.

06:45.013 --> 06:46.710
Miss Farrow, I'm-I'm so sorry

06:46.754 --> 06:49.017
for the loss of your friend.

06:49.931 --> 06:51.498
You were good friends,
weren't you?

06:51.541 --> 06:53.108
We were.

06:53.151 --> 06:55.458
So you knew she had a heart
condition? Tachycardia.

06:55.502 --> 06:57.547
-Can you tell us...
-Objection, Your Honor. That has

06:57.591 --> 06:59.419
-Objection. Under the eggsh...
-nothing to do
with what we're...

06:59.462 --> 07:01.899
Wait, wait, wait, wait. You're
on the same side, you two.

07:03.510 --> 07:06.991
Your Honor, under the eggshell
doctrine, it is irrelevant

07:07.035 --> 07:08.645
whether Antoinette
had a heart condition.

07:08.689 --> 07:12.432
What does matter is that the
defendant caused the injury.

07:12.475 --> 07:14.346
Your Honor, we would argue
that the stun gun

07:14.390 --> 07:16.218
wasn't the true cause of death.
Her heart condition was.

07:16.261 --> 07:18.307
Okay, well, good for you two.

07:18.350 --> 07:20.396
You both got your statements
out to the jury.

07:20.440 --> 07:23.094
Overruled.
The defense may argue causation.

07:23.138 --> 07:25.183
-Please continue.
-Ms. Farrow,

07:25.227 --> 07:26.576
did Antoinette's heart condition

07:26.620 --> 07:29.187
mean she was supposed
to avoid overexertion?

07:29.231 --> 07:32.060
She had a heart arrhythmia,
but she was careful.

07:32.103 --> 07:35.542
That cop put 50,000 volts
through her.

07:35.585 --> 07:36.717
Right, that cop.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.327
Let's talk about that cop.

07:38.370 --> 07:40.677
Ms. Farrow, this is your
Instagram profile, isn't it?

07:40.721 --> 07:41.983
-Object-Obj...
-Objection.

07:42.026 --> 07:43.550
Okay.
Give me a hint, Counselors.

07:43.593 --> 07:45.421
-Relevance.
-This is inflammatory.
-Okay, okay.

07:45.465 --> 07:47.510
So, what is going on over there?
Do you need separate tables?

07:47.554 --> 07:49.599
-No, Your Honor.
-Just objection.
-You must know what's coming,

07:49.643 --> 07:52.123
because I don't.
Overruled.

07:52.167 --> 07:55.518
On Instagram, you quote
these rap lyrics,

07:55.562 --> 07:58.042
"Fuck the cops like porn stars,

07:58.086 --> 08:00.044
keeping us caged behind bars."

08:00.088 --> 08:01.655
Objection, Your Honor.

08:01.698 --> 08:02.873
It speaks to the witness' bias.

08:02.917 --> 08:04.222
To quote rap lyrics?
No.

08:04.266 --> 08:06.529
No. That shows
the counselor's racism.

08:06.573 --> 08:09.010
Oh, that's right, everything
you don't like is racist.

08:09.053 --> 08:11.360
The Supreme Court ruled
that rap lyrics can be

08:11.403 --> 08:14.058
-considered criminal evidence.
-No, they merely
declined to reverse.

08:14.102 --> 08:15.799
And you're going
one step further

08:15.843 --> 08:17.366
to damn someone
who quotes the lyrics.

08:17.409 --> 08:20.064
-I'm not damning.
-Okay, I'm-I'm gonna talk now.

08:20.108 --> 08:22.632
I don't like this like this line
of reasoning, Counselor.

08:22.676 --> 08:26.506
I have quoted Johnny Cash's song
about shooting a man in Reno.

08:26.549 --> 08:28.769
Does that go to my character?
I hope not.

08:28.812 --> 08:32.033
Sustained.
Let's move on.

08:32.860 --> 08:35.558
Professors expect students
to be respectful.

08:35.602 --> 08:37.299
I don't think
it's too much to expect

08:37.342 --> 08:39.997
that our teachers
be respectful in return.

08:40.781 --> 08:42.434
Okay, got it.

08:42.478 --> 08:44.045
And that irritated you?

08:44.088 --> 08:45.699
It more than irritated me.

08:45.742 --> 08:47.265
I-I found the word offensive.

08:47.309 --> 08:50.486
So you decided to call Professor
Henrietta Michaels out?

08:50.530 --> 08:52.749
Well, I just reported it.

08:52.793 --> 08:54.316
I mean, the word
is self-explanatory.

08:54.359 --> 08:57.188
-It's a triggering word.
-Here's the text of your tweet.

08:57.232 --> 08:59.103
Can you read it for His Honor?

08:59.147 --> 09:02.411
"How does Professor Michaels
think it's okay in 2021

09:02.454 --> 09:04.761
to use a word so similar
to the N-word?"

09:04.805 --> 09:07.372
So, at this point, I think we
need to talk about the word

09:07.416 --> 09:09.549
itself and how we're gonna
continue to refer to it.

09:09.592 --> 09:12.029
Our handy graphics team
at Copy Coop--

09:12.073 --> 09:14.858
20% off on all large orders
until Friday--

09:14.902 --> 09:17.557
has put the word on our display.

09:18.601 --> 09:19.820
That's the word.

09:19.863 --> 09:21.473
I feel like a little duck
should come down.

09:21.517 --> 09:22.866
"You say the magic word,
you collect a $100."

09:24.476 --> 09:26.870
Sorry, millennials,
you can look that one up.

09:26.914 --> 09:29.307
Anyway, from now on,

09:29.351 --> 09:33.398
I think we should refer
to the word as...

09:33.442 --> 09:35.226
um...

09:35.270 --> 09:36.880
I don't know.
Thoughts?

09:36.924 --> 09:39.056
N-word-ly?

09:39.100 --> 09:40.971
-Inelegant, but sure.
Uh, Your Honor,

09:41.015 --> 09:44.801
defense feels that
any euphemism for the word

09:44.845 --> 09:47.195
in question, uh,
biases the court against

09:47.238 --> 09:50.677
my client's honest use
of said word.

09:50.720 --> 09:53.593
"Said word?" Seriously?

09:53.636 --> 09:57.161
-It's powdered-wig time,
my friend.
-Oh, no. Your Honor, really?

09:57.205 --> 10:00.034
No obtuse use
of language or Latin.

10:00.077 --> 10:02.036
You know the penalty.

10:02.863 --> 10:04.299
Thank you, Dean.

10:04.342 --> 10:06.301
Very becoming.
Since I am

10:06.344 --> 10:09.043
the court, I will swear to you,

10:09.086 --> 10:11.175
I will not be biased
by said word.

10:11.219 --> 10:13.700
"N-word-ly" it is.

10:13.743 --> 10:15.484
Go ahead, Prosecutor.

10:15.527 --> 10:17.965
And you found
her use of that word--

10:18.008 --> 10:21.664
-notice I didn't say
"said word."
-Always in awe, Counselor.

10:21.708 --> 10:22.883
You found it offensive?

10:22.926 --> 10:24.798
Yes.

10:24.841 --> 10:26.887
Good.
I think that's it.

10:26.930 --> 10:28.366
No more questions.

10:28.410 --> 10:30.673
<i>-De lege lata.</i> That was a joke.
-I don't care.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.283
-That's why we have two. Dean.
-No, no, no,

10:32.327 --> 10:35.069
-that was a joke, I... No.
-Come on, Marissa.

10:35.112 --> 10:37.201
Now, Camille,
you are aware the word--

10:37.245 --> 10:38.855
-what is it?
-N-word-ly.

10:38.899 --> 10:42.380
N-word-ly-- you are aware
that it simply means "stingy"?

10:42.424 --> 10:44.034
-Right?
Yes.

10:44.078 --> 10:45.862
And that it comes from
an Old Norse word,

10:45.906 --> 10:47.951
"nigla," meaning "poor"

10:47.995 --> 10:52.173
-and it has the same root
as the word "niggle"?
-Yes.

10:52.216 --> 10:54.915
So, if Professor Michaels
had said the word "niggle"

10:54.958 --> 10:57.395
-would you have felt offended?
-No.

10:57.439 --> 10:59.484
-Why not?
-It wouldn't sound like

10:59.528 --> 11:01.704
-the "N-word."
-So it doesn't matter

11:01.748 --> 11:03.445
that the word in question

11:03.488 --> 11:05.577
has no racial connotations
whatsoever?

11:05.621 --> 11:07.884
Given how it sounds,
the word definitely

11:07.928 --> 11:09.494
has racial connotations,

11:09.538 --> 11:11.105
whether you're prepared
to acknowledge that or not.

11:11.148 --> 11:14.195
But the etymology
of the word is non-racial.

11:14.238 --> 11:16.371
I'm not an expert in etymology,

11:16.414 --> 11:19.722
but I do know something about
people using the N-word.

11:20.854 --> 11:24.509
Camille, before you tweeted
about Professor Michaels'

11:24.553 --> 11:26.598
use of N-word-ly,

11:26.642 --> 11:29.253
wasn't there something else
she did that upset you?

11:29.297 --> 11:32.256
I'm not sure what
you're talking about.
Well, you asked her twice

11:32.300 --> 11:34.302
for an extension
on your term paper.

11:37.784 --> 11:38.915
Yeah-huh.

11:38.959 --> 11:40.264
And she said no.

11:40.308 --> 11:43.485
And when you did
turn in the term paper late

11:43.528 --> 11:46.227
anyway, what grade did you get?

11:46.270 --> 11:47.750
-She gave me a C.
And isn't that

11:47.794 --> 11:50.884
really the reason that
you wanted to get her fired?

11:50.927 --> 11:52.276
No.

11:52.320 --> 11:53.756
Can't you object or something?

11:53.800 --> 11:56.716
-This has nothing to do with it.
-Even if she did object,

11:56.759 --> 11:58.195
you'd still have to
answer the question.

11:58.239 --> 11:59.762
This court is bullshit.

11:59.806 --> 12:02.243
You want to clear her
so she can get her job back,

12:02.286 --> 12:04.201
but she knew what she was doing
using that word.

12:04.245 --> 12:06.508
-No, I didn't.
-Come on.

12:06.551 --> 12:09.206
You think college is meant
to be a warm, cuddly place

12:09.250 --> 12:10.730
-where you're not challenged.
-No,

12:10.773 --> 12:13.558
I just don't want to spend
my day being offended.

12:13.602 --> 12:15.778
These are the words that
make up the English language.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.519
They exist.

12:17.562 --> 12:19.869
They don't mean
what you think they mean.

12:19.913 --> 12:21.784
-And that is education.
-No.

12:21.828 --> 12:25.788
An education is living in now,
not in the 16th century.

12:25.832 --> 12:28.486
Okay, good. That was
illuminating.

12:28.530 --> 12:30.706
You can step down now.
Thank you, my dear.

12:36.407 --> 12:38.670
Fuck you.
You're not even trying.

12:47.070 --> 12:49.116
