15:07.341 --> 15:09.560
Never, and...

15:09.604 --> 15:11.693
I hope to God I never do again.

15:11.736 --> 15:13.651
Did anyone tell you

15:13.695 --> 15:15.523
that Antoinette Lacey
had a heart condition?

15:15.566 --> 15:19.135
No. No one did.

15:19.179 --> 15:21.181
I just...

15:30.190 --> 15:32.148
So, other than
killing an unarmed girl,

15:32.192 --> 15:34.977
Object to "killed."
-you never used your stun gun?

15:35.021 --> 15:37.458
-Yeah, Counselor, rephrase.
So, other than using

15:37.501 --> 15:39.764
lethal force on an unarmed girl,

15:39.808 --> 15:42.158
you only faced
disciplinary action

15:42.202 --> 15:43.638
for violent behavior once?

15:43.681 --> 15:45.248
I'm not sure
what you're referring to.

15:45.292 --> 15:47.947
In February, 2019,

15:47.990 --> 15:50.862
did Chicago PD
respond to a report

15:50.906 --> 15:52.560
of a domestic dispute
at your house?

15:52.603 --> 15:54.344
Objection.
Your Honor, Officer McFinley

15:54.388 --> 15:55.955
isn't on trial
for his personal life.

15:55.998 --> 15:58.392
No, he's on trial
for being a violent cop.

15:58.435 --> 16:00.524
Overruled.
The witness may answer.

16:01.395 --> 16:03.136
It wasn't...

16:03.179 --> 16:04.702
It was an argument.

16:04.746 --> 16:05.965
My wife...

16:06.008 --> 16:07.009
My ex-wife...

16:07.053 --> 16:08.706
We had a fight,

16:08.750 --> 16:10.404
not a physical one, verbal.

16:10.447 --> 16:13.276
-So it was
just a noise disturbance?
-Yes.

16:13.320 --> 16:15.887
-Your Honor...
-Uh, Your... Your Honor,

16:15.931 --> 16:18.020
we would like
to call our next witness,

16:18.064 --> 16:19.456
Officer McFinley's ex-wife,

16:19.500 --> 16:20.849
-Vanessa McFinley.
Your Honor,

16:20.892 --> 16:22.590
Ms. McFinley was not
on the witness list.

16:22.633 --> 16:24.505
She doesn't need to be.
She's being used

16:24.548 --> 16:26.898
to rebut
Officer McFinley's testimony.

16:26.942 --> 16:29.205
-The testimony he just swore to.
-I'm sorry, just a moment,

16:29.249 --> 16:31.425
-Ms. McFinley.
Your Honor,
I know that

16:31.468 --> 16:32.904
with your politics you lean

16:32.948 --> 16:34.819
-to the worldview of BLM...
-No, no,

16:34.863 --> 16:36.473
Counselor, please
don't try that.

16:36.517 --> 16:38.649
Then we ask for a recess
to review with our client.

16:38.693 --> 16:40.216
They can review all they want.

16:40.260 --> 16:42.784
It's not gonna change
what's been said on the stand.

16:42.827 --> 16:45.004
Well, still, Ms. Reddick, um...

16:45.047 --> 16:47.528
let's adjourn
to tomorrow morning.

16:49.573 --> 16:52.315
Well, it was a good try
to get her in today.

16:52.359 --> 16:53.882
Yeah, well,
whether we get her in today

16:53.925 --> 16:57.320
or tomorrow, it doesn't matter.
She's a slam dunk.

17:02.847 --> 17:04.197
Nicholas Dupont.

17:04.240 --> 17:05.807
I represent comedians.

17:06.634 --> 17:09.332
I want to help anyone
who's serious about comedy

17:09.376 --> 17:10.638
and his career.

17:12.379 --> 17:14.946
-His career but not her career?
-I... Uh, no, that's-that's not

17:14.990 --> 17:16.948
-what I was trying to say.
-One for

17:16.992 --> 17:19.168
the prosecution, Dean.
No, no, wait.
Now, she didn't

17:19.212 --> 17:21.779
-let me finish my statement.
-Yes, she did, sir.

17:21.823 --> 17:24.739
And you revealed your mindset
with a spontaneous utterance.

17:24.782 --> 17:26.393
Continue, Madame Prosecutor.

17:26.436 --> 17:28.960
-Miss Prosecutor.
-Miss, my apologies.

17:29.004 --> 17:31.398
Your clients
include Joey Battle.
That's right.

17:31.441 --> 17:32.790
He's a very talented man.

17:32.834 --> 17:35.315
One of the funniest men alive.

17:36.142 --> 17:38.753
Did doing your best for Joey
mean silencing

17:38.796 --> 17:40.494
June Barrow
after he victimized her?

17:40.537 --> 17:42.365
Uh, objection to victimized.

17:42.409 --> 17:44.802
You only get three objections
per day in my court, Mr. Cord.

17:44.846 --> 17:46.195
You sure you want to use it now?

17:46.239 --> 17:47.544
Uh...

17:47.588 --> 17:49.285
Objection withdrawn.

17:49.329 --> 17:51.331
I never silenced anyone.

17:51.374 --> 17:55.552
I have here an affidavit from
Steve Brant at the Laugh Farm

17:55.596 --> 17:57.380
saying you explicitly told him

17:57.424 --> 17:59.252
to cancel June's
upcoming booking.

17:59.295 --> 18:01.384
Eh, he hates me.
Uh-huh. And you

18:01.428 --> 18:02.907
-apparently hate him.
-Look,

18:02.951 --> 18:04.648
I might have called her
a loose cannon.

18:04.692 --> 18:06.520
That's a possibilit...

18:06.563 --> 18:08.652
Look, uh...

18:08.696 --> 18:11.655
at the time, I had no idea
there was any truth

18:11.699 --> 18:13.570
-to the allegations about Joey.
-You didn't notice

18:13.614 --> 18:15.572
that June's story
had uncanny similarities

18:15.616 --> 18:17.922
to stories told
by other female comedians?

18:17.966 --> 18:20.099
I heard a rumor that Joey
might have had an affair or two

18:20.142 --> 18:21.665
that went sour, but...

18:21.709 --> 18:25.582
I-I didn't understand
the allegations, exactly.

18:25.626 --> 18:27.106
You never heard
that he had a habit

18:27.149 --> 18:29.064
of inviting women
to his dressing room,

18:29.108 --> 18:31.110
blocking the door,
and then masturbating

18:31.153 --> 18:33.416
-into a potted ficus?
-Absolutely not.

18:33.460 --> 18:36.158
So it's just a coincidence that
at your 2015 holiday party

18:36.202 --> 18:37.855
you made a joke
that people should keep Joey

18:37.899 --> 18:40.075
away from the Christmas tree?

18:43.644 --> 18:47.691
I think this deserves
two slashes, Dean.

18:49.084 --> 18:50.651
Marissa.

18:50.694 --> 18:53.001
Use me however you want.
I'm in.

18:53.044 --> 18:54.176
-Really?
-Yes.

18:54.220 --> 18:56.787
Oh!
Thank you.

18:56.831 --> 18:58.180
Hey.

18:58.224 --> 19:00.617
Where was that passion
in the N-word case?

19:01.749 --> 19:04.969
Oh, I guess I feel like
it's not the N-word.

19:05.013 --> 19:06.319
It is.

19:06.362 --> 19:08.451
It always is.

19:38.786 --> 19:41.484
<i>Witnesses heard the shooter
yell, "That's for Antoinette,"</i>

19:41.528 --> 19:44.226
<i>-an apparent reference
to the ongoing
-Oh, my God.</i>

19:44.270 --> 19:45.836
<i>-civil suit against the officer.
-Diane, turn on the news.</i>

19:45.880 --> 19:47.534
<i>In what is turning into
a season of...</i>

19:49.405 --> 19:53.192
<i>Before two shots
were fired at close range.</i>

19:53.235 --> 19:55.150
<i>The assailant is unknown
and still at large.</i>

19:55.194 --> 19:57.587
<i>Many wonder whether
the ongoing brutality lawsuit</i>

19:57.631 --> 19:59.589
<i>against the city
had something to do with</i>

19:59.633 --> 20:02.113
<i>the patrol officer's murder.</i>

20:02.157 --> 20:03.941
Oh, fuck.

20:03.985 --> 20:06.944
<i>Jesse McFinley was a father
of four and a 15-year veteran</i>

20:06.988 --> 20:09.643
<i>of the Chicago
Police Department.</i>

21:55.096 --> 21:56.619
Do you guys have a minute?

21:56.663 --> 21:57.925
Sure.

22:00.275 --> 22:02.059
Remember how you told me
how much you hate

22:02.103 --> 22:03.409
being Blackopedia
for white people,

22:03.452 --> 22:04.975
explaining what is
or isn't offensive?

22:05.019 --> 22:06.586
Yeah.

22:06.629 --> 22:09.806
I really need to ask you if
something is or isn't offensive.

22:11.808 --> 22:13.723
We love playing this game
with white allies.

22:13.767 --> 22:15.377
You can ask me about Jews
any time you want.

22:15.421 --> 22:16.596
Just go.

22:18.075 --> 22:19.816
I'm prosecuting someone
in Wackner's court

22:19.860 --> 22:21.731
who lost their professorship
for saying a word.

22:21.775 --> 22:24.038
What word?

22:28.521 --> 22:29.652
Niggardly?

22:29.696 --> 22:30.784
As in "stingy"?

22:30.827 --> 22:32.960
Exactly. Is the word offensive?

22:33.003 --> 22:35.615
-No. It means stingy.
-Wait...

22:35.658 --> 22:36.920
It's a medieval word

22:36.964 --> 22:38.879
that no one uses
in casual conversation.

22:38.922 --> 22:41.403
-You really think
it's offensive?
-I think it's a microaggression.

22:41.447 --> 22:43.100
And microaggressions
are like Pringles.

22:43.144 --> 22:45.320
You never have just one.
If you mean "stingy"...

22:45.364 --> 22:47.148
But don't you undercut
the English language

22:47.191 --> 22:49.150
when you reduce the number
of words we can use?

22:49.193 --> 22:50.281
Then create new ones!

22:50.325 --> 22:51.587
That's how language develops.

22:51.631 --> 22:53.894
-Why not do both?
-Okay.

22:53.937 --> 22:56.287
-African Americans aren't
monolithic. I get it.

22:56.331 --> 22:58.072
-No, Carmen is just weird.
-No.

22:58.115 --> 23:00.988
I just don't have the same
thin skin that you do.

23:01.031 --> 23:02.859
-Really? Thin?
Uh-huh.

23:02.903 --> 23:04.905
Not a Black person on earth
would ever let that word slide.

23:04.948 --> 23:07.168
Thank you for supporting
the monolithic argument,

23:07.211 --> 23:09.388
but I think it has nothing
to do with that.

23:10.214 --> 23:13.479
Although I've asked you
to ignore the news,

23:13.522 --> 23:18.005
you've probably heard by now
that Officer McFinley

23:18.048 --> 23:20.442
-was killed last night.

23:20.486 --> 23:23.358
Our deepest sympathies
go out to his family.

23:23.402 --> 23:27.144
Nevertheless, uh,
this case is not against him,

23:27.188 --> 23:29.930
it is against the Chicago PD.

23:29.973 --> 23:34.021
We must do our best
to set aside emotions

23:34.064 --> 23:36.415
and look only at the facts.

23:36.458 --> 23:37.764
But first...

23:37.807 --> 23:40.114
a moment of silence

23:40.157 --> 23:43.465
feels appropriate.

23:54.824 --> 23:57.174
We're fucked.

23:58.088 --> 24:01.309
Thank you for answering
our questions, Ms. McFinley.

24:02.092 --> 24:05.182
Can you tell us about your
ex-husband's violence

24:05.226 --> 24:07.576
and the domestic abuse call?

24:08.751 --> 24:10.971
He was a good man.

24:12.668 --> 24:14.061
When he got stressed out,

24:14.104 --> 24:16.498
it was only 'cause he
was working too hard.

24:16.542 --> 24:20.328
He put his life on the line
every single day.

24:20.371 --> 24:23.113
But he-he, he did hit you?

24:23.157 --> 24:25.725
I'm so sorry, Jess.

24:25.768 --> 24:27.988
I'm so sorry. Oh, my God.

24:28.031 --> 24:29.511
You didn't deserve it.

24:37.171 --> 24:39.913
Mr. McFinley's death,
in the middle of this case,

24:39.956 --> 24:41.741
has clearly prejudiced
this jury.

24:41.784 --> 24:43.003
Why would you think that?

24:43.046 --> 24:44.265
Oh, come on.

24:44.308 --> 24:45.745
Not a great argument, Counselor.

24:45.788 --> 24:47.703
I'm going to need something
more than "Come on."

24:47.747 --> 24:48.835
We're worried that the jury

24:48.878 --> 24:50.358
won't base their decision
on fact.

24:50.401 --> 24:51.925
They're gonna base it on
McFinley being violently killed.

24:51.968 --> 24:53.535
You were never basing this
on the facts.

24:53.579 --> 24:54.928
You were basing this
on the emotions

24:54.971 --> 24:56.233
for that poor Black girl.

24:56.277 --> 24:57.844
-Okay, thank you.

24:57.887 --> 24:59.715
I'm-I'm just gonna keep
talking until somebody listens.

24:59.759 --> 25:02.239
So, I'm just talking, talking.
Words, words, words.

25:02.283 --> 25:04.154
I'm calling a voir dire de novo.

25:04.198 --> 25:05.808
I know. I know.

25:05.852 --> 25:07.331
I've never done this before.

25:07.375 --> 25:09.072
A voir dire, mid-trial,

25:09.116 --> 25:10.987
you can re-question
the jury in chambers.

25:11.031 --> 25:12.902
You can ask them if they're
watching the news

25:12.946 --> 25:14.600
and find out
how they're impacted.

25:14.643 --> 25:17.298
And if they are impacted,
you will declare a mistrial?

25:17.341 --> 25:18.560
I don't know what I'll do.

25:18.604 --> 25:20.606
You can solve this, though.
You know?

25:20.649 --> 25:25.219
You three can come up with some
kind of negotiated settlement.

25:25.262 --> 25:26.263
That's my recommendation.

25:26.307 --> 25:28.570
But what do I know?

25:28.614 --> 25:32.052
Joey invited comedians
to his dressing room for drinks

25:32.095 --> 25:33.793
after shows sometimes.

25:33.836 --> 25:35.055
Hey, Joey.

25:35.098 --> 25:36.970
I was excited
when he invited me.

25:37.013 --> 25:39.233
I thought, finally,
I'm in the inner circle.

25:39.276 --> 25:41.931
