from a prior gig on July 10th.

26:40.903 --> 26:44.385
"While June Barrow has been
described as a rising star,

26:44.428 --> 26:47.431
"she proved tonight
how easy it is to mistake

26:47.475 --> 26:49.433
a low-flying satellite
for a distant sun."

26:49.477 --> 26:51.653
Ms. Barrow, your headliner gig

26:51.697 --> 26:53.524
was canceled
because of bad reviews.

26:53.568 --> 26:55.352
-Wasn't it?
-Comics get bad reviews
all the time.

26:55.396 --> 26:56.745
Have you read Joey Battle's?

26:56.789 --> 26:58.617
Well, why don't you show us
your act then?

26:58.660 --> 27:00.053
Let the court see
just how funny you are.

27:00.096 --> 27:01.489
-Objection.

27:01.532 --> 27:03.273
That sounds like a good idea.

27:03.317 --> 27:04.492
It's irrelevant, Your Honor.

27:04.535 --> 27:06.450
This is the wrong venue,
the wrong crowd.

27:06.494 --> 27:08.322
You-You've gotten tons
of laughs in here.

27:08.365 --> 27:10.106
They were spontaneous.
This is different.

27:10.150 --> 27:12.674
Marissa, you're flailing.

27:12.718 --> 27:14.545
You know what you get
when you flail.

27:14.589 --> 27:15.982
I... Your Honor,
I am not flailing.

27:16.025 --> 27:17.810
Put it on, Marissa.

27:17.853 --> 27:19.594
Come on.

27:20.943 --> 27:23.685
Okay, be seated.

27:23.729 --> 27:26.470
Okay, let's hear it.
Tell us some jokes.

27:26.514 --> 27:29.386
-I'm not really a joke comedian.
-What other kind is there?

27:29.430 --> 27:32.694
I tell stories about the frailty
of being human.

27:32.738 --> 27:34.304
Oh, okay. Do that.

27:35.088 --> 27:37.220
Uh...

27:38.308 --> 27:40.789
Ah, okay, uh...

27:40.833 --> 27:44.706
Uh, who came up
with the term "rape fantasy"?

27:44.750 --> 27:48.362
I mean, what was that woman
thinking? She should aim higher.

27:48.405 --> 27:50.190
One day I'm gonna win
an Oscar and cure cancer,

27:50.233 --> 27:52.540
-and then...

27:52.583 --> 27:54.934
I love being a millennial.

27:54.977 --> 27:58.546
I can wake up late and blame
everyone else for everything.

28:03.812 --> 28:05.074
Okay, Dean.

28:08.469 --> 28:11.080
Have a seat in the,
uh, witness box,

28:11.124 --> 28:13.517
Juror Number Two.

28:13.561 --> 28:16.564
So, uh, the attorneys are
gonna ask you some questions

28:16.607 --> 28:19.306
about recent events to see
how you've been affected.

28:19.349 --> 28:20.829
Is that okay?

28:20.873 --> 28:24.485
You posted on Facebook
after the McFinley killing.

28:24.528 --> 28:25.747
-Didn't you?
-I guess.

28:25.791 --> 28:27.836
I talk to my grandkids
every day.

28:27.880 --> 28:29.229
Mm-hmm. You wrote,

28:29.272 --> 28:32.188
"People need to have respect
for what cops do.

28:32.232 --> 28:34.103
A hero was gunned down."

28:34.147 --> 28:35.757
I just think he deserves
a little respect.

28:35.801 --> 28:37.324
The man died.

28:37.367 --> 28:39.282
-Your Honor, we move
to strike for cause.
-Objection.

28:39.326 --> 28:40.762
This is all racial.

28:40.806 --> 28:43.678
It is not. She wrote
in support of McFinley.

28:43.722 --> 28:46.333
Yeah. Yeah, I'll give it to you.
Uh, juror dismissed.

28:46.376 --> 28:47.900
Let's get the next one in here.

28:47.943 --> 28:49.510
Thank you. Thank you.

28:51.251 --> 28:53.688
Didn't three Black students
approach you

28:53.732 --> 28:55.734
about not repeating the word
"N-word-ly"?

28:55.777 --> 28:59.259
Oh, they objected to many
of the ways I taught.

28:59.302 --> 29:02.349
And, despite that,
you used the word again,

29:02.392 --> 29:04.351
even though you were told
it made them uncomfortable?

29:04.394 --> 29:06.788
Objection. Unduly argumentative.

29:06.832 --> 29:08.529
She didn't commit murder.

29:08.572 --> 29:11.445
True, but I love a good
Socratic argument. Go for it.

29:11.488 --> 29:13.403
You used "N-word-ly" again,
didn't you, Professor?

29:15.666 --> 29:18.408
I took it as a teaching moment.

29:18.452 --> 29:21.150
I-I explained
what the word meant,

29:21.194 --> 29:24.284
and, uh, I had to use the word
in order to explain it.

29:24.327 --> 29:25.328
Even though
you were asked to stop?

29:25.372 --> 29:26.765
I'm an educator.

29:26.808 --> 29:28.941
Challenging students
is my responsibility.

29:28.984 --> 29:30.377
So you're trying to offend?

29:30.420 --> 29:33.075
No, but I am trying to prepare
my students

29:33.119 --> 29:36.122
for a world that won't kowtow
to their sensitivities.

29:36.165 --> 29:39.778
So you deliberately say things
to trigger students?

29:39.821 --> 29:42.563
School is not a place
to be comforted.

29:42.606 --> 29:43.956
It's a place to be challenged.

29:43.999 --> 29:46.915
Where do you draw the line
between challenged

29:46.959 --> 29:48.177
and triggered?

29:48.221 --> 29:49.352
I don't.

29:49.396 --> 29:50.963
A-a-a class shouldn't be
governed

29:51.006 --> 29:52.878
by the most fragile sensibility,

29:52.921 --> 29:56.882
or, or it would shy away
from every difficult subject.

29:56.925 --> 29:59.928
A history class
has to discuss rape

29:59.972 --> 30:01.669
when talking about war crimes.

30:01.712 --> 30:03.584
But it doesn't have
to describe it in detail.

30:03.627 --> 30:06.674
It does if it wants
the students to sympathize,

30:06.717 --> 30:09.285
to understand
a victim's account.

30:09.329 --> 30:11.984
The only way to honor a victim

30:12.027 --> 30:14.638
might be to relate
to her full account.

30:15.901 --> 30:17.598
Okay, I get that.

30:17.641 --> 30:20.557
But why not use
the word "stingy"

30:20.601 --> 30:24.692
or "miserly"
instead of "N-word-ly"?

30:24.735 --> 30:27.608
Because I like clarity
in language.

30:27.651 --> 30:29.436
I like variety in language.

30:29.479 --> 30:33.527
And, and-and, yes,
maybe I am pushing back a bit.

30:33.570 --> 30:34.876
Then why not use the N-word?

30:34.920 --> 30:37.400
Could we have one questioner
at a time?

30:37.444 --> 30:38.967
No, answer the question.

30:39.011 --> 30:41.404
If you want to push back,
why not use the actual N-word?

30:42.231 --> 30:46.670
Because I'm not teaching the
Civil War or <i>Huckleberry Finn.</i>

30:46.714 --> 30:48.934
And if you were, you might?

30:50.761 --> 30:52.328
Yes.

30:53.895 --> 30:55.114
Juror 14.

30:55.157 --> 30:57.594
Identifies as mixed race.

30:57.638 --> 30:59.205
Works at a food bank.

30:59.248 --> 31:00.946
Probably won't be able
to knock him off.

31:00.989 --> 31:02.512
We're out of options.

31:02.556 --> 31:05.037
We need one more juror
bumped to get our mistrial.

31:05.080 --> 31:07.387
-I've checked. We don't
have anything else.

31:07.430 --> 31:09.476
You need to see this.

31:09.519 --> 31:10.912
Oh, good God. What now?

31:10.956 --> 31:12.218
We're on the news.

31:12.261 --> 31:14.046
On? What does that mean?

31:14.089 --> 31:16.396
<i>Systemic racism.
White privilege.</i>

31:16.439 --> 31:20.226
<i>We hear it from academics
and Hollywood celebrities</i>

31:20.269 --> 31:21.923
<i>and basketball players.</i>

31:21.967 --> 31:24.012
<i>By the way, how many houses
does LeBron James have?</i>

31:24.056 --> 31:27.581
<i>Now add to the list
Marxist slip-and-fall lawyers</i>

31:27.624 --> 31:29.931
-<i>from "Raddick"/
-Lockhart.</i>

31:29.975 --> 31:32.629
<i>You need to hear what one
of these lawyers had to say</i>

31:32.673 --> 31:34.631
about martyred Chicago
police officer

31:34.675 --> 31:36.590
Jesse Patrick McFinley.

31:36.633 --> 31:39.419
Cops have not been held
accountable for far too long,

31:39.462 --> 31:41.508
and now the bill is due.

31:41.551 --> 31:44.337
I made that statement
before McFinley was killed.

31:44.380 --> 31:46.774
A cop gunned down in cold blood.

31:46.817 --> 31:48.776
And to lawyer Diane Lockhart,

31:48.819 --> 31:51.387
-Oh... <i>
-"The bill's come due."</i>

31:51.431 --> 31:53.433
<i>Was that not her finger
on the trigger</i>

31:53.476 --> 31:57.089
as much as whatever thug
held the gun?

31:57.132 --> 31:58.612
<i>I'm asking the question</i>

31:58.655 --> 32:01.397
<i>because that's what we do here.</i>

32:03.443 --> 32:04.966
Maybe we could use this.

32:08.013 --> 32:09.275
With the judge?

32:09.318 --> 32:11.146
He hates Fox News.

32:11.190 --> 32:13.061
Maybe we could start over
again with the jurors.

32:13.105 --> 32:16.586
Well, I'm glad you find
something positive here.

32:16.630 --> 32:19.328
He just called you two
co-assassins.

32:19.372 --> 32:21.765
We need to get you security.

32:30.383 --> 32:32.167
So one more juror.

32:32.211 --> 32:34.126
And we have our mistrial.

32:34.169 --> 32:35.605
That's doable.

32:39.740 --> 32:42.395
Stay close.

33:12.381 --> 33:13.948
All rise.

33:17.778 --> 33:19.649
May we approach, Your Honor?

33:20.563 --> 33:22.652
Uh, sure. Yeah. Let's go ahead.

33:22.696 --> 33:25.394
You may be seated. Thank you.

33:28.354 --> 33:31.444
Your Honor, last night
Ted Willoughby on Fox News...

33:31.487 --> 33:33.011
Yes, I-I know who he is.

33:33.054 --> 33:34.838
He accused the two of us
of being complicit

33:34.882 --> 33:36.884
in the murder
of Officer McFinley...

33:36.927 --> 33:38.799
Was this the first time someone
on Fox was mean to you?

33:38.842 --> 33:41.802
We're concerned about
his influence on the jury.

33:41.845 --> 33:43.586
We'd like to ask the jurors
about it.

33:43.630 --> 33:45.545
Your Honor, we already went
through the jurors.

33:45.588 --> 33:47.590
You ruled no mistrial.

33:47.634 --> 33:49.201
This is new influence.

33:49.244 --> 33:50.941
They just want another bite
at the apple.

33:50.985 --> 33:52.508
They want to get
one more juror bumped.

33:52.552 --> 33:55.076
We want an unbiased jury
just like you do.

33:55.120 --> 33:56.556
Just like His Honor does.

33:56.599 --> 33:58.993
And we don't want
the influence of Fox News.

33:59.037 --> 34:00.647
They're playing
on your bias against Fox.

34:00.690 --> 34:05.565
Okay, uh, voir dire de novo
et doctuse.

34:05.608 --> 34:08.002
That's Latin for "the sequel."

34:09.786 --> 34:12.050
Do you know who
Ted Willoughby is?

34:12.093 --> 34:12.963
I do.

34:13.007 --> 34:14.182
And have you watched his show?

34:14.226 --> 34:15.749
Not has she watched his show,

34:15.792 --> 34:17.707
but has she watched his show
last night?

34:17.751 --> 34:19.100
Okay, I'll ask.

34:19.144 --> 34:20.449
Have you watched
the Ted Willoughby show

34:20.493 --> 34:21.450
in the last two days?

34:21.494 --> 34:22.582
Uh, no, I don't watch it.

34:22.625 --> 34:24.584
Some people from my church have,

34:24.627 --> 34:25.933
but I don't like it.

34:25.976 --> 34:27.587
And has anyone from your church
told you

34:27.630 --> 34:29.110
that Ted Willoughby said
that the two of us

34:29.154 --> 34:30.503
are responsible
for the murder...

34:30.546 --> 34:31.895
She just said she didn't see it.

34:31.939 --> 34:33.114
Don't try to fill her in
and create some bias

34:33.158 --> 34:34.724
where there is none.

34:34.768 --> 34:36.248
We take exception to that
characterization, Your Honor.

34:36.291 --> 34:37.945
No, no, no, no, no, no.
Come here. All of you.

34:37.988 --> 34:40.817
Uh, no, sorry. Not you.
Uh, sorry, stay.

34:40.861 --> 34:43.124
Um, Counselors,
you two are pushing it.

34:43.168 --> 34:45.083
You get to ask these jurors
one question.

34:45.126 --> 34:47.085
Have they seen this reporter?
And that's it.

34:47.128 --> 34:49.130
And whether they're intimidated
by the presence of cops

34:49.174 --> 34:50.653
-in the courtroom.
-Your Honor...

34:50.697 --> 34:52.133
No, that's
a reasonable question.

34:52.177 --> 34:54.657
And if we get noes
from the jurors, we move on.

34:54.701 --> 34:56.964
-Understood?
Yes.

34:57.007 --> 34:59.140
That didn't go well.

34:59.184 --> 35:00.620
Okay. What now?

35:00.663 --> 35:02.187
Prepare for trial.

35:02.230 --> 35:03.971
I'll see if the jurors' answers
check out.

35:06.191 --> 35:08.584
This is odd.
The case I didn't care about

35:08.628 --> 35:11.413
is going well, and the one
I do care about is cratering.

35:11.457 --> 35:12.893
-Did you see that guy?
-No.

35:12.936 --> 35:15.548
-What?
-It was Joey Battle.

35:19.682 --> 35:21.423
What was Joey Battle doing here?

35:21.467 --> 35:22.859
He met with David Lee.

35:22.903 --> 35:25.166
He's negotiating a contract
with Del Cooper.

35:27.864 --> 35:29.866
Del Cooper to the stand.

35:29.910 --> 35:31.651
I'm sorry, you want...

35:31.694 --> 35:33.174
Del Cooper.

35:33.218 --> 35:36.134
I know he can hear me,
he's in the control room.

35:37.396 --> 35:38.832
Ah. See? Here he comes.

35:38.875 --> 35:40.442
Hey, Hal, uh, Your Honor,

35:40.486 --> 35:42.618
look, I'm really needed
in the control room right now.

35:42.662 --> 35:44.490
If this is a TV show, yes.

35:44.533 --> 35:46.187
But if this is a court, no.

35:47.580 --> 35:49.016
Step up here, Del.

35:55.065 --> 35:57.764
If I take the stand, then
I'm breaking the fourth wall,

35:57.807 --> 35:59.244
and we don't want to do that.

35:59.287 --> 36:00.984
Nobody's breaking any walls.

36:01.028 --> 36:03.944
Sit down in the chair, and
let her ask whatever she wants.

36:06.251 --> 36:08.209
Mr. Cooper,
you had a conversation

36:08.253 --> 36:10.342
with Judge Wackner
prior to this trial, didn't you?

36:10.385 --> 36:12.648
-Objection.
-You were part of that
conversation, Mr. Cord.

36:12.692 --> 36:14.041
So were you.

36:14.084 --> 36:15.999
Exactly. So we all
have to be honest here.

36:16.043 --> 36:19.307
Mr. Cooper,
you encouraged Judge Wackner

36:19.351 --> 36:21.353
to take this Joey Battle case,
didn't you?

36:21.396 --> 36:22.919
I have to object, Your Honor.

36:22.963 --> 36:24.225
This court is entitled
to adjudicate any dispute...

36:24.269 --> 36:25.879
Where are you going with this,
Marissa?

36:25.922 --> 36:27.533
Mr. Cooper, you hoped
to rehabilitate

36:27.576 --> 36:29.883
Joey Battle's career,
isn't that right?

36:29.926 --> 36:32.320
So you could put him back
on your streaming site

36:32.364 --> 36:35.193
for a stand-up you're recording
in St. Louis in 14 days?

36:36.237 --> 36:37.412
No.

36:37.456 --> 36:39.371
I thought it would be good
for this show.

36:39.414 --> 36:41.068
This show?

36:41.111 --> 36:43.723
This show,
meaning Wackner's court?

36:43.766 --> 36:45.420
-This is a mistake, Marissa.
-Is it?

36:45.464 --> 36:47.901
Aren't we just here to discover
the truth, Your Honor?

36:47.944 --> 36:50.120
You have something to say
to me, just say it.

36:50.164 --> 36:52.775
Have you prejudged this case?

36:54.299 --> 36:56.649
Are you questioning
my integrity?

36:56.692 --> 36:57.867
I'm asking if you pre...

36:57.911 --> 36:59.782
No, goddamn it!

36:59.826 --> 37:04.613
You will answer my question
before you ask me yours.

37:04.657 --> 37:07.094
If you've already decided how
this case will end,

37:07.137 --> 37:09.183
Your Honor, if we're here
to give Del the ending

37:09.227 --> 37:11.359
he wants for his TV show
and to make you rich and famous,

37:11.403 --> 37:13.579
-then, yes, I am questioning
your integrity.
-Put the cameras on.

37:13.622 --> 37:16.495
You pack up your things and you
get the fuck out of here.

37:16.538 --> 37:21.282
The women who have trusted this
court deserve representation.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.849
Well,
you should've thought of that

37:22.892 --> 37:24.285
before you ran off
your fucking mouth.

37:24.329 --> 37:26.374
Now, you get the hell
out of my courtroom!

37:29.159 --> 37:31.161
Wow.

38:15.380 --> 38:17.033
Oh, my God.

38:19.514 --> 38:20.776
It happened last night.

38:20.820 --> 38:22.648
Security doesn't know
how they got in.

38:22.691 --> 38:23.823
Of course they don't.

38:23.866 --> 38:25.564
They suggest we call the cops.

38:25.607 --> 38:27.653
We're gonna have to paint.

38:27.696 --> 38:29.176
I called building maintenance.

38:29.219 --> 38:31.352
-They say we may have to wait.
-What? Why?

38:31.396 --> 38:33.093
'Cause we're cop killers.

38:33.876 --> 38:35.008
Liz, Diane...

38:35.051 --> 38:37.184
I think you might want to see

38:37.227 --> 38:38.664
what Ted Willoughby's
been saying lately.

38:38.707 --> 38:40.796
I think we get the idea, Julius.

38:40.840 --> 38:43.451
No, this is something else.

38:43.495 --> 38:47.063
<i>The man who gave his life
to protect his fellow citizens</i>

38:47.107 --> 38:50.458
<i>is dead, but that's not enough
for the two lawyers</i>

38:50.502 --> 38:52.199
<i>spitting on his grave.</i>

38:52.242 --> 38:54.375
<i>The militant Elizabeth Reddick,</i>

38:54.419 --> 38:57.073
<i>daughter of a disgraced
civil rights leader,</i>

38:57.117 --> 39:00.033
<i>and liberal looney tune
Diane Lockhart.</i>

39:00.076 --> 39:03.036
<i>If the name Diane Lockhart
sounds familiar to you,</i>

39:03.079 --> 39:04.994
<i>that may be
because of my colleague</i>

39:05.038 --> 39:07.040
<i>Duke Roscoe's discovery.</i>

39:07.083 --> 39:11.218
<i>He outed her 11 years ago
as a closeted lesbian.</i>

39:11.261 --> 39:14.439
<i>Diane Lockhart
is technically married,</i>

39:14.482 --> 39:17.616
<i>but to a man we rarely see.
