39:17.659 --> 39:20.140
<i>Could it be that she
has something more in common</i>

39:20.183 --> 39:22.534
<i>with someone else?</i>

39:22.577 --> 39:24.144
<i>Someone she works with?</i>

39:24.187 --> 39:27.539
<i>She and Liz Reddick
appear to be inseparable.</i>

39:27.582 --> 39:29.758
<i>Is Liz Reddick
Diane Lockhart's new lover?</i>

39:31.456 --> 39:33.371
<i>I'm just asking questions.
There's no way to know for sure,</i>

39:33.414 --> 39:37.026
<i>because Diane Lockhart
and Liz Reddick won't tell us.</i>

39:38.506 --> 39:40.421
<i>These two lipstick lawyers
want the jury to</i>

39:40.465 --> 39:44.120
<i>believe their eyes when they
look at fuzzy cell phone videos.</i>

39:44.164 --> 39:46.688
<i>Why don't they want us
to believe our eyes</i>

39:46.732 --> 39:48.429
<i>when we look at them?</i>

39:59.701 --> 40:00.876
So...

40:00.920 --> 40:03.313
When do I get to meet your son?

40:05.490 --> 40:06.578
I don't know.

40:06.621 --> 40:07.666
Are we that serious?

40:07.709 --> 40:10.495
I don't know. You tell me.

40:10.538 --> 40:11.931
How's Diane?

40:11.974 --> 40:13.585
Mm-hmm.

40:13.628 --> 40:16.588
So, you're telling me,
I have nothing to worry about?

40:16.631 --> 40:17.763
Okay, Diane and I,

40:17.806 --> 40:19.242
-we go a long way back.
-Mm-hmm.

40:19.286 --> 40:21.244
All right? We didn't
become lovers until after

40:21.288 --> 40:24.247
Trump was elected. It was a very
experimental thing.

40:25.466 --> 40:27.773
Yeah, so, uh...
This is a bit, right?

40:27.816 --> 40:30.253
-Yeah, you'll never know.
-Mm-hmm.

40:30.297 --> 40:31.646
I have ways of making you talk.

40:37.870 --> 40:40.350
Shit.

40:40.394 --> 40:42.309
Yeah, it's me.

40:42.352 --> 40:43.789
No.

40:43.832 --> 40:45.878
No, no, no. You tell him "no."

40:45.921 --> 40:47.619
I-I don't care
if it's contractual.

40:47.662 --> 40:50.622
All right? I'm coming down
right now.

40:50.665 --> 40:51.797
Who was that?

40:51.840 --> 40:53.929
That is my secret lover.

40:53.973 --> 40:56.889
-Huh?
-My, uh, latest reality star.

40:56.932 --> 40:59.152
-Yeah.
-Come here.

41:00.501 --> 41:02.242
Mm.

41:02.285 --> 41:05.680
<i>Are you questioning
my integrity?</i>

41:05.724 --> 41:08.509
<i>-I'm asking if you've pre...
-No, goddamn it!</i>

41:08.553 --> 41:12.644
<i>You will answer my question
before you ask me yours.</i>

41:12.687 --> 41:14.472
<i>If you've already decided</i>

41:14.515 --> 41:16.430
<i>how this case will end,
Your Honor,</i>

41:16.474 --> 41:18.519
<i>if we're here to give Del
the ending he wants</i>

41:18.563 --> 41:20.521
<i>for his TV show,
and to make you rich and famous,</i>

41:20.565 --> 41:23.481
<i>then yes,
I am questioning your integrity.</i>

41:23.524 --> 41:25.657
<i>You pack up your things,
and you get the...</i>

41:25.700 --> 41:27.963
Hey, hey, hey, man.

41:28.007 --> 41:29.399
-Judge.
-Hmm?

41:29.443 --> 41:30.531
Look...

41:30.575 --> 41:32.751
you lost your temper.
Okay?

41:32.794 --> 41:34.796
It's no big deal.

41:34.840 --> 41:36.537
I'm Pol Pot.

41:36.581 --> 41:38.844
-I'm Ceausescu.
No. No.

41:38.887 --> 41:40.454
Man, look.

41:40.498 --> 41:43.457
One of the biggest moments
in reality TV history

41:43.501 --> 41:47.983
was Tyra Banks losing her shit
on <i>America's Top Model.</i>

41:48.027 --> 41:50.464
She had a meltdown.
Meltdowns are good TV.

41:52.205 --> 41:54.381
Pick up, Marissa. Pick up.

41:54.424 --> 41:56.514
Come on. Come on.

41:56.557 --> 41:58.037
Pick up.

42:05.435 --> 42:06.741
I'm here.

42:06.785 --> 42:09.048
Hey...

42:09.091 --> 42:11.006
I want you to come back
to court.

42:11.050 --> 42:12.399
<i>I want you to finish your cases.</i>

42:12.442 --> 42:13.661
Why?

42:13.705 --> 42:15.881
Because I made a mistake.

42:15.924 --> 42:17.578
I was an asshole.

42:17.622 --> 42:18.710
You were right.

42:18.753 --> 42:20.581
<i>Do you want me to apologize?</i>

42:20.625 --> 42:21.843
<i>I will.</i>

42:21.887 --> 42:23.584
Yeah, actually, I do.

42:23.628 --> 42:26.065
I'm sorry.

42:26.108 --> 42:28.023
I was biased.

42:28.067 --> 42:31.200
<i>I won't be when you come back.</i>

42:31.244 --> 42:33.638
I'm taking this seriously,
Your Honor.

42:33.681 --> 42:35.204
I know you are.

42:35.248 --> 42:37.206
That's why I want you back.

42:37.250 --> 42:39.469
You got to finish it.

42:44.649 --> 42:45.911
Thank you. Come in.

42:45.954 --> 42:50.655
Uh, hey.
Thank you for stopping by.

42:50.698 --> 42:52.613
Um...

42:52.657 --> 42:54.528
I...

42:54.572 --> 42:57.575
I've been worried that
I was insensitive,

42:57.618 --> 43:00.186
and I wanted to get
a gut check from both of you.

43:00.229 --> 43:02.318
Sure, Your Honor. What is it?

43:02.362 --> 43:04.190
I've been watching the two
of you throughout the case,

43:04.233 --> 43:06.366
and I realized,
after what I heard last night,

43:06.409 --> 43:09.108
that, uh, your discomfort...

43:09.151 --> 43:11.806
made sense to me.

43:12.677 --> 43:17.290
If my wife and I ever
tried to work together,

43:17.333 --> 43:18.987
our relationship wouldn't last

43:19.031 --> 43:21.468
ten minutes.

43:21.511 --> 43:24.384
So, yeah, more power to you.

43:24.427 --> 43:27.300
I just... I'm a great friend
of the LGBTQ,

43:27.343 --> 43:30.695
uh, plus, you know, community.

43:30.738 --> 43:33.175
Thank you, Your Honor.

43:34.829 --> 43:36.831
Yeah, um...

43:36.875 --> 43:38.528
Yeah, actually, you know what?

43:38.572 --> 43:40.792
Your Honor, there is, there is
something that you could...

43:40.835 --> 43:42.750
could settle for us.

43:42.794 --> 43:44.317
Oh, great. Certainly. Yeah.

43:44.360 --> 43:46.798
One of the jurors, uh,
the one from the church?

43:47.712 --> 43:50.497
Uh, I think she's noticed
how close we are together.

43:50.540 --> 43:51.977
And, uh...

43:52.020 --> 43:53.500
I-I hope you
don't mind me saying this.

43:53.543 --> 43:55.981
No, it's been on my mind
as well. She did...

43:56.024 --> 43:58.070
She did see us
out in the hall...

43:58.113 --> 43:59.506
Yeah.
-...together.

43:59.549 --> 44:01.987
Yeah, and, uh, uh,
we're just worried

44:02.030 --> 44:05.164
that our relationship
may have played into her bias.

44:05.207 --> 44:07.906
It would just be good
to be certain.

44:07.949 --> 44:10.125
Don't you think, darling?

44:14.564 --> 44:16.001
So, you go ahead
and ask your questions.

44:16.044 --> 44:17.567
Show what a terrible
person I am.

44:17.611 --> 44:21.049
I guarantee you, I already know,
so does everyone else.

44:21.093 --> 44:23.356
Yeah, that's
sort of your schtick,

44:23.399 --> 44:25.184
saying how awful you are.

44:25.227 --> 44:27.708
My schtick? No, it's the,
the voices in my head.

44:27.752 --> 44:29.405
No. Oof.

44:29.449 --> 44:31.407
-I'm an asshole. Good one.

44:31.451 --> 44:33.758
Seems like you feel
pretty sorry for yourself.

44:33.801 --> 44:35.411
I do? I'm sorry.

44:35.455 --> 44:39.024
But you don't feel sorry for
how you treat other people.

44:39.067 --> 44:40.852
Is that a question?

44:40.895 --> 44:43.463
<i>You want to make it
in this business? Be ruthless.</i>

44:43.506 --> 44:45.508
<i>The only thing that matters
is your material.</i>

44:45.552 --> 44:47.859
<i>Other people, they're not real.</i>

44:47.902 --> 44:50.949
<i>You can't worry
about their feelings.</i>

44:50.992 --> 44:52.298
<i>The minute you care...</i>

44:52.341 --> 44:54.387
<i>comedy dies.</i>

44:54.430 --> 44:56.519
"Other people are not real."

44:56.563 --> 44:59.435
That was four years ago.
I'm a different person.

44:59.479 --> 45:02.134
Two nights ago,
you did a set at 2:00 a.m.

45:02.177 --> 45:03.613
at The Side Room downtown.

45:03.657 --> 45:06.268
I-I was testing out
some material.

45:06.312 --> 45:08.488
Trying some stuff out.

45:08.531 --> 45:10.185
<i>So there's all these
stupid women out there</i>

45:10.229 --> 45:14.407
<i>who are going around saying,
"Oh, he did awful things to me."</i>

45:14.450 --> 45:17.323
<i>Which just makes it harder,
in this day and age,</i>

45:17.366 --> 45:20.413
<i>for me to convince other women
to let me do awful things</i>

45:20.456 --> 45:21.762
<i>to them,
which I want to do because</i>

45:21.806 --> 45:23.982
<i>-I'm a male human being!</i>

45:24.025 --> 45:25.853
<i>You'd think people would
understand that by now,</i>

45:25.897 --> 45:28.595
<i>but they seem to be completely
hung up on the whole...</i>

45:28.638 --> 45:31.250
<i>"doing awful things" aspect.</i>

45:31.293 --> 45:32.817
Is that the new you?

45:32.860 --> 45:34.079
No.

45:34.122 --> 45:35.428
That is... Look.

45:35.471 --> 45:37.647
Comedy, it's, um...

45:37.691 --> 45:38.910
I do bits.

45:38.953 --> 45:40.781
It's a mercurial, kind of...

45:40.825 --> 45:42.827
They're not real.
It's not, you know, it's...

45:42.870 --> 45:46.178
What you got to look at is
they're just a whatchamacall--

45:46.221 --> 45:47.875
Like a-- Ah.

45:53.446 --> 45:54.926
The time has come.

45:54.969 --> 45:56.275
I am ready to rule.

45:57.232 --> 45:59.321
Henrietta, you were born free,

45:59.365 --> 46:01.628
and I return you
to your natural state.

46:02.977 --> 46:04.065
What does that mean?

46:04.109 --> 46:05.284
It means you may go.

46:05.327 --> 46:07.286
What you did
falls under the category

46:07.329 --> 46:08.940
of "awful but lawful."

46:08.983 --> 46:11.638
And we here at
the Circuit Court of 9 3/4

46:11.681 --> 46:14.684
are not in the business of
regulating manners.

46:14.728 --> 46:15.947
So, goodbye.

46:15.990 --> 46:18.819
Your Honor,
that's actually not what I want.

46:18.863 --> 46:20.386
It isn't?

46:20.429 --> 46:21.648
What does that mean?

46:21.691 --> 46:24.216
It would help me get my job back

46:24.259 --> 46:26.218
if the school knew
I was being punished.

46:26.261 --> 46:27.959
You want to be punished?

46:28.002 --> 46:29.351
Yes, please.

46:29.395 --> 46:32.311
It's the only way
I can be uncanceled.

46:32.354 --> 46:35.096
If they know the canceling
was satisfied.

46:35.140 --> 46:38.056
I have only one word for that...

46:38.099 --> 46:39.448
Oy.

46:39.492 --> 46:43.496
But sure.
I penalize you to, um...

46:43.539 --> 46:45.541
cleaning the school bathrooms
for a week.

46:46.368 --> 46:48.022
-Thank you, Your Honor.
-Anytime.

46:48.066 --> 46:50.285
-Good luck.

46:50.329 --> 46:51.373
And now Joey Battle.

46:51.417 --> 46:53.071
Yes, Your Honor. Yes.

46:53.114 --> 46:56.465
Joey, as you can see, the score
really isn't in your favor.

46:56.509 --> 46:58.206
I understand you want
your career back.

46:58.250 --> 47:00.556
You are a funny man.

47:00.600 --> 47:02.210
It takes hard work to get funny.

47:02.254 --> 47:03.864
Maybe you think that's enough.

47:03.908 --> 47:07.085
But you haven't done anything
for the women you hurt.

47:07.128 --> 47:08.347
You haven't made amends.

47:08.390 --> 47:10.088
Your Honor, I...

47:10.131 --> 47:11.829
I brought my checkbook.

47:11.872 --> 47:13.482
You're a rich man, Joey.
I think everyone here

47:13.526 --> 47:15.006
knows the minute
you go back to work,

47:15.049 --> 47:16.834
you'll earn back your fine
in no time.

47:16.877 --> 47:19.619
Your Honor, everybody deserves
a second chance.

47:19.662 --> 47:21.708
You know the expression,
"doing your time"?

47:21.751 --> 47:24.711
Your Honor, I haven't worked
a major venue in over a year.

47:24.754 --> 47:27.235
How much time
do you want me to take?

47:27.279 --> 47:31.544
Doing time means more than
taking time.

47:31.587 --> 47:33.851
It means serving your sentence.

47:33.894 --> 47:35.200
Going to prison.

47:35.243 --> 47:37.506
You want to come back? Okay.

47:37.550 --> 47:39.944
First, you got to do your time.

47:39.987 --> 47:42.033
Three-week sentence.

47:42.076 --> 47:43.382
June.

47:43.425 --> 47:45.036
-Yes?
-Please.

47:45.079 --> 47:47.560
Come. Here you go.

47:47.603 --> 47:49.040
Go ahead. Cuff him.

47:49.083 --> 47:51.303
Is this some kind of a metaphor
or something?

47:51.346 --> 47:53.044
-Like an adult time-out?
-Yes, Joey.

47:53.087 --> 47:55.655
That's exactly what prison is,
an adult time-out.

47:55.698 --> 47:58.049
You keep saying pri-- Uh,
this is a joke, though, right?

47:58.092 --> 48:01.226
June.
I said cuff him.

48:01.269 --> 48:02.575
Now.

48:02.618 --> 48:04.925
Your Honor,
you can't just send him...

48:04.969 --> 48:07.362
W-What prison
are you talking about?

48:07.406 --> 48:08.537
There is no prison.

48:08.581 --> 48:10.104
Oh, boy, there is.

48:10.148 --> 48:12.933
This court's benefactor
owns a private prison company.

48:12.977 --> 48:16.763
He's offered us a wing in one
of his bankrupted institutions.

48:16.806 --> 48:18.591
Lucky you, Joey.

48:18.634 --> 48:19.940
You're the first person
I'm sending there.

48:19.984 --> 48:21.594
Oh, my God.

48:21.637 --> 48:23.422
June, he harmed you.

48:23.465 --> 48:25.815
Go ahead. Cuff him.

48:29.036 --> 48:31.430
You're going to escort him
to his cell.

48:31.473 --> 48:32.910
In this court, you get to see

48:32.953 --> 48:34.999
the person you're sending away,
eye to eye.

48:35.042 --> 48:36.435
Hey, Your Honor.

48:36.478 --> 48:38.785
Let's, uh...
let's make it two weeks, okay?

48:38.828 --> 48:42.180
I know. You have your
stand-up in St. Louis.

48:42.223 --> 48:43.790
Three weeks.

48:43.833 --> 48:45.313
-Recess,

48:45.357 --> 48:48.316
then we have
the Exxon Mobile case.

49:08.597 --> 49:10.295
This is really happening,
isn't it?

49:10.338 --> 49:11.992
It sure looks like it.

49:27.529 --> 49:29.575
Turn around.

49:37.365 --> 49:40.281
June...

49:40.325 --> 49:41.891
I'm sorry.

49:44.068 --> 49:45.460
You're forgiven.

50:04.697 --> 50:06.960
Good afternoon, ladies.

50:07.004 --> 50:09.441
Thanks for coming in
on short notice.

50:12.096 --> 50:15.969
I hear there's been a lot
of tension between you two.

50:16.752 --> 50:18.711
No, everything's fine.

50:18.754 --> 50:21.192
Oh, good to know.

50:21.235 --> 50:26.762
Well, Human Resources
needs you two to sign these.

50:32.464 --> 50:34.074
A love contract?

50:34.118 --> 50:35.249
Yes.

50:35.293 --> 50:37.773
When employees
embark on a relationship,

50:37.817 --> 50:39.993
it's policy for us to confirm,
in writing,

50:40.037 --> 50:42.561
that the relationship
is consensual.

50:43.823 --> 50:46.869
We in H.R. just want to avoid
problems later.

50:46.913 --> 50:50.656
Sometimes romances
don't work out.

51:03.364 --> 51:04.931
Good.

51:04.974 --> 51:07.412
Good. I hope you two
patch things up.

51:07.455 --> 51:10.371
This is the first step.

